    "category": "arithmetic",
    "title": "Integer Overflow in add()",
    "evidence": {
      "file": "contract.sol",
      "lines": [11],
      "function": "add"
    },
    "explanation": "In Solidity 0.4.25, arithmetic operations do not revert on overflow. The statement `balance += deposit;` can wrap around modulo 2^256 when `deposit` is large enough. For example, calling `add(uint256(-1))` will set `balance` from 1 to 0, allowing an attacker to manipulate the stored `balance` arbitrarily."
